  "excerpt": "Small, half-moon pastry pies filled with a thick sour cherry filling and sealed at the edge with a crimp before baking. The pastry is an all-butter shortcrust; the filling is made from sour cherries cooked briefly with sugar until jammy and glossy. The hand size format means no tin is needed: they are formed on a lined baking tray and hold their own shape.",
