  "sourceNotes": "Small hand-held pastry pies filled with fruit are documented in British and American baking literature from at least the eighteenth century. Hannah Glasse, The Art of Cookery Made Plain and Easy (1747, public domain and available at Project Gutenberg), describes small pastry cases filled with fruit. The sour cherry filling variant is described in American and British domestic baking guides from the early twentieth century, with sour cherries commonly used as a pie filling in these traditions.",
