            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the filling and pastry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cook the cherries with the sugar and lemon juice in a small saucepan over medium heat for 8 to 10 minutes until the fruit softens and the syrup thickens. Stir in the flour and cook for 1 more minute. Tip into a bowl and cool completely. Make the pastry by rubbing the cold butter into the flour, sugar, and salt. Add the egg and cold water and bring together into a dough. Wrap and chill for 1 hour."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assemble and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C conventional (180°C fan). Line a baking tray. Roll the pastry to about 3 mm thick and cut into 12 cm rounds. Place a generous tablespoon of the cooled cherry filling on one half of each round, leaving a 1 cm border. Fold the other half over and press the edge firmly with a fork to seal. Place on the tray, cut a small steam vent in the top of each, brush with egg wash, and sprinkle with caster sugar. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until deep golden. Cool on a rack."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
